AD-03  Route configuration loaded from wdp.api_route PostgreSQL table at startup
       via R2DBC. Cached by CachingRouteLocator. Route changes require pod restart.

AD-04  DB is queried TWICE at startup: (1) blocking collectList().block() in
       AuthenticationFilter.createWhiteList() for the JWT whitelist; (2) reactive
       query in ApiPathRouteLocatorImpl for route predicates.

AD-05  authExceptions column: comma-delimited string, split on literal comma,
       no trim on split results, resulting entries matched via Spring Security
       pathMatchers() using Ant-style matching.

AD-06  Four filters execute in this order: (1) Spring Security JWT authentication,
       (2) LoggingGlobalFilter at order = -1, (3) AuthorizationFilter at order = 0,
       (4) CaseNumberFilter at order = 0. Steps 3 and 4 share order = 0 with no
       secondary ordering mechanism — execution is non-deterministic.

AD-07  LoggingGlobalFilter: inbound pass logs request path and matched route ID.
       Outbound pass (after chain returns) logs the same inbound path and HTTP
       response status code. Does not log response time. Does not inspect body.
       NPE thrown if route attribute is null on inbound pass.

AD-08  AuthorizationFilter: region detected by case-insensitive substring match
       on exactly four constants /US/, /UK/, /PIN/, /NAP/. Firm type via iss
       claim substring check for us_worldpay_fis_int. Missing AuthorizationList
       JWT claim causes NPE producing 500. Empty role intersection returns 403
       with empty body.

AD-09  CaseNumberFilter: case ID detection requires path segment of exactly 12
       characters, first character alphabetic, exactly 2 alphabetic characters
       total across all 12. NAP platform calls UAMS /authorize. PIN platform
       calls CHAS /authorize. Internal firm (iss contains us_worldpay_fis_int)
       is auto-authorized with no external call. If platform resolves to null
       or is not NAP or PIN, isAuthorized remains null and the method returns
       true — implicit auto-authorization without any external call.

AD-10  /entity-authorize endpoint is never called. entityHierarchy parameter
       is always null. The routing capability exists in RestInvoker but has no
       active call path from any filter.

AD-11  Both UAMS and CHAS outbound calls: blocking RestTemplate with no
       ClientHttpRequestFactory, no connection timeout configured, no read timeout
       configured, no retry, no circuit breaker. Original caller JWT forwarded
       as-is in Authorization header. Response type is void — pass/fail via
       HTTP status code only. Non-2xx or exception returns 403 empty body.

AD-12  CORE, VAP, and LATAM are not present anywhere in the gateway source as
